            "id": "10edf80fc78e46919b232",
            "questionText": "A muon is created in the upper atmosphere at an altitude of 10 km ($!$10 \\times 10^3 \\text{ m}$!$) above the Earth's surface. The muon has a proper half-life of 2.2 microseconds ($!$2.2 \\times 10^{-6} \\text{ s}$!$) and is traveling towards the Earth at a speed of 0.99$!$c$!$, where $!$c$!$ is the speed of light. Accounting for time dilation, determine the average distance the muon will travel as observed from Earth before it decays.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "aa5fd7a2bb8f4e10ab5e9",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining the Lorentz factor. Please select the correct formula that relates the velocity $!$v$!$ and the speed of light $!$c$!$ for computing $!$\\gamma$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "a0d65d2b-9a39-4a41-bda5-09be98a1c66a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\gamma = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{1 - \\frac{v^2}{c^2}}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\gamma = \\sqrt{1 - \\frac{v^2}{c^2}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\gamma = 1 - \\frac{v^2}{c^2}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "912cffeddf0c4a9890a9a",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, using the value of $!$\\gamma$!$ you obtained, calculate the dilated half-life in the Earth frame by multiplying $!$\\gamma$!$ with the proper half-life ($!$2.2 \\times 10^{-6} \\text{ s}$!$). What is the dilated half-life?",
